{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":815,"text":"I'd like to talk today"},{"time":2450,"text":"about how we can change our brains"},{"time":4922,"text":"and our society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7515,"text":"Meet Joe."},{"time":9690,"text":"Joe's 32 years old and a murderer."},{"time":13408,"text":"I met Joe 13 years ago on the lifer wing"},{"time":16150,"text":"at Wormwood Scrubs high-security prison in London."},{"time":19970,"text":"I'd like you to imagine this place."},{"time":21971,"text":"It looks and feels like it sounds:"},{"time":25069,"text":"Wormwood Scrubs."},{"time":27451,"text":"Built at the end of the Victorian Era"},{"time":29675,"text":"by the inmates themselves,"},{"time":31187,"text":"it is where England's most\ndangerous prisoners are kept."},{"time":34387,"text":"These individuals have committed acts"},{"time":36593,"text":"of unspeakable evil."},{"time":38763,"text":"And I was there to study their brains."},{"time":42474,"text":"I was part of a team of researchers"},{"time":44226,"text":"from University College London,"},{"time":45903,"text":"on a grant from the U.K. department of health."},{"time":48658,"text":"My task was to study a group of inmates"},{"time":50706,"text":"who had been clinically diagnosed as psychopaths."},{"time":53450,"text":"That meant they were the most"},{"time":55175,"text":"callous and the most aggressive"},{"time":56888,"text":"of the entire prison population."},{"time":60012,"text":"What lay at the root of their behavior?"},{"time":63589,"text":"Was there a neurological cause for their condition?"},{"time":67915,"text":"And if there was a neurological cause,"},{"time":70758,"text":"could we find a cure?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73813,"text":"So I'd like to speak about change, and \nespecially about emotional change."},{"time":77758,"text":"Growing up, I was always intrigued"},{"time":79738,"text":"by how people change."},{"time":82802,"text":"My mother, a clinical psychotherapist,"},{"time":85325,"text":"would occasionally see patients at home"},{"time":87965,"text":"in the evening."},{"time":89385,"text":"She would shut the door to the living room,"},{"time":90919,"text":"and I imagined"},{"time":92924,"text":"magical things happened in that room."},{"time":95436,"text":"At the age of five or six"},{"time":97117,"text":"I would creep up in my pajamas"},{"time":99559,"text":"and sit outside with my ear glued to the door."},{"time":102368,"text":"On more than one occasion, I fell asleep"},{"time":103815,"text":"and they had to push me out of the way"},{"time":105275,"text":"at the end of the session."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107436,"text":"And I suppose that's how I found myself"},{"time":110335,"text":"walking into the secure interview room"},{"time":112410,"text":"on my first day at Wormwood Scrubs."},{"time":116419,"text":"Joe sat across a steel table"},{"time":118755,"text":"and greeted me with this blank expression."},{"time":122981,"text":"The prison warden, looking equally indifferent,"},{"time":125859,"text":"said, \"Any trouble, just press the red buzzer,"},{"time":128506,"text":"and we'll be around as soon as we can.\""},{"time":130945,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133903,"text":"I sat down."},{"time":135673,"text":"The heavy metal door slammed shut behind me."},{"time":138650,"text":"I looked up at the red buzzer"},{"time":140744,"text":"far behind Joe on the opposite wall."},{"time":142843,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145489,"text":"I looked at Joe."},{"time":147251,"text":"Perhaps detecting my concern,"},{"time":149328,"text":"he leaned forward, and said,"},{"time":150684,"text":"as reassuringly as he could,"},{"time":152911,"text":"\"Ah, don't worry about the buzzer,"},{"time":154291,"text":"it doesn't work anyway.\""},{"time":156544,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":163472,"text":"Over the subsequent months,"},{"time":165361,"text":"we tested Joe and his fellow inmates,"},{"time":169446,"text":"looking specifically at their ability"},{"time":171497,"text":"to categorize different images of emotion."},{"time":176481,"text":"And we looked at their physical response"},{"time":178267,"text":"to those emotions."},{"time":180009,"text":"So, for example, when most of us look"},{"time":181590,"text":"at a picture like this of somebody looking sad,"},{"time":184515,"text":"we instantly have a slight,"},{"time":188066,"text":"measurable physical response:"},{"time":190000,"text":"increased heart rate, sweating of the skin."},{"time":193298,"text":"Whilst the psychopaths in our study were able"},{"time":195082,"text":"to describe the pictures accurately,"},{"time":197096,"text":"they failed to show the emotions required."},{"time":200829,"text":"They failed to show a physical response."},{"time":204382,"text":"It was as though they knew the words"},{"time":206433,"text":"but not the music of empathy."},{"time":209826,"text":"So we wanted to look closer at this"},{"time":211610,"text":"to use MRI to image their brains."},{"time":215059,"text":"That turned out to be not such an easy task."},{"time":218166,"text":"Imagine transporting a collection"},{"time":219995,"text":"of clinical psychopaths across central London"},{"time":222690,"text":"in shackles and handcuffs"},{"time":224829,"text":"in rush hour,"},{"time":226955,"text":"and in order to place each\nof them in an MRI scanner,"},{"time":230129,"text":"you have to remove all metal objects,"},{"time":232110,"text":"including shackles and handcuffs,"},{"time":233444,"text":"and, as I learned, all body piercings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237799,"text":"After some time, however,\nwe had a tentative answer."},{"time":242036,"text":"These individuals were not just the victims"},{"time":244854,"text":"of a troubled childhood."},{"time":246906,"text":"There was something else."},{"time":249427,"text":"People like Joe have a deficit in a brain area"},{"time":253047,"text":"called the amygdala."},{"time":255108,"text":"The amygdala is an almond-shaped organ"},{"time":257132,"text":"deep within each of the hemispheres of the brain."},{"time":260455,"text":"It is thought to be key to the experience of empathy."},{"time":264940,"text":"Normally, the more empathic a person is,"},{"time":267846,"text":"the larger and more active their amygdala is."},{"time":270891,"text":"Our population of inmates"},{"time":272371,"text":"had a deficient amygdala,"},{"time":273698,"text":"which likely led to their lack of empathy"},{"time":275993,"text":"and to their immoral behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278927,"text":"So let's take a step back."},{"time":282069,"text":"Normally, acquiring moral behavior"},{"time":284692,"text":"is simply part of growing up,"},{"time":287082,"text":"like learning to speak."},{"time":289283,"text":"At the age of six months, virtually every one of us"},{"time":292574,"text":"is able to differentiate between\nanimate and inanimate objects."},{"time":296531,"text":"At the age of 12 months,"},{"time":299005,"text":"most children are able to imitate"},{"time":302229,"text":"the purposeful actions of others."},{"time":304114,"text":"So for example, your mother raises her hands"},{"time":306649,"text":"to stretch, and you imitate her behavior."},{"time":309388,"text":"At first, this isn't perfect."},{"time":312589,"text":"I remember my cousin Sasha,"},{"time":314536,"text":"two years old at the time,"},{"time":316699,"text":"looking through a picture book"},{"time":318359,"text":"and licking one finger and flicking\nthe page with the other hand,"},{"time":321542,"text":"licking one finger and flicking\nthe page with the other hand."},{"time":323647,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":325961,"text":"Bit by bit, we build the foundations \nof the social brain"},{"time":329887,"text":"so that by the time we're three, four years old,"},{"time":334519,"text":"most children, not all,"},{"time":335811,"text":"have acquired the ability to understand"},{"time":337584,"text":"the intentions of others,"},{"time":339187,"text":"another prerequisite for empathy."},{"time":342513,"text":"The fact that this developmental progression"},{"time":345125,"text":"is universal,"},{"time":346627,"text":"irrespective of where you live in the world"},{"time":348603,"text":"or which culture you inhabit,"},{"time":351229,"text":"strongly suggests that the foundations"},{"time":353442,"text":"of moral behavior are inborn."},{"time":356566,"text":"If you doubt this,"},{"time":359043,"text":"try, as I've done, to renege on a promise you've made"},{"time":362819,"text":"to a four-year-old."},{"time":364896,"text":"You will find that the mind of a four-year old"},{"time":366684,"text":"is not na√Øve in the slightest."},{"time":368188,"text":"It is more akin to a Swiss army knife"},{"time":371213,"text":"with fixed mental modules"},{"time":373244,"text":"finely honed during development"},{"time":375718,"text":"and a sharp sense of fairness."},{"time":378835,"text":"The early years are crucial."},{"time":381493,"text":"There seems to be a window of opportunity,"},{"time":383737,"text":"after which mastering moral questions"},{"time":386203,"text":"becomes more difficult,"},{"time":387685,"text":"like adults learning a foreign language."},{"time":391819,"text":"That's not to say it's impossible."},{"time":393853,"text":"A recent, wonderful study from Stanford University"},{"time":396962,"text":"showed that people who have played"},{"time":399203,"text":"a virtual reality game in which they took on"},{"time":401612,"text":"the role of a good and helpful superhero"},{"time":404073,"text":"actually became more caring and helpful"},{"time":406189,"text":"towards others afterwards."},{"time":408692,"text":"Now I'm not suggesting"},{"time":410901,"text":"we endow criminals with superpowers,"},{"time":413956,"text":"but I am suggesting that we need to find ways"},{"time":417369,"text":"to get Joe and people like him"},{"time":419247,"text":"to change their brains and their behavior,"},{"time":421892,"text":"for their benefit"},{"time":423667,"text":"and for the benefit of the rest of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426802,"text":"So can brains change?"},{"time":430337,"text":"For over 100 years,"},{"time":432921,"text":"neuroanatomists and later neuroscientists"},{"time":436035,"text":"held the view that after initial\ndevelopment in childhood,"},{"time":439855,"text":"no new brain cells could grow"},{"time":442279,"text":"in the adult human brain."},{"time":443580,"text":"The brain could only change"},{"time":445067,"text":"within certain set limits."},{"time":447049,"text":"That was the dogma."},{"time":449147,"text":"But then, in the 1990s,"},{"time":451386,"text":"studies starting showing,"},{"time":453082,"text":"following the lead of Elizabeth\nGould at Princeton and others,"},{"time":455819,"text":"studies started showing the\nevidence of neurogenesis,"},{"time":459154,"text":"the birth of new brain cells"},{"time":461212,"text":"in the adult mammalian brain,"},{"time":464281,"text":"first in the olfactory bulb,"},{"time":465865,"text":"which is responsible for our sense of smell,"},{"time":467946,"text":"then in the hippocampus"},{"time":469985,"text":"involving short-term memory,"},{"time":472029,"text":"and finally in the amygdala itself."},{"time":475312,"text":"In order to understand"},{"time":477088,"text":"how this process works,"},{"time":479047,"text":"I left the psychopaths and joined a lab in Oxford"},{"time":481936,"text":"specializing in learning and development."},{"time":485198,"text":"Instead of psychopaths, I studied mice,"},{"time":488968,"text":"because the same pattern of brain responses"},{"time":491309,"text":"appears across many different\nspecies of social animals."},{"time":495039,"text":"So if you rear a mouse in a standard cage,"},{"time":499621,"text":"a shoebox, essentially, with cotton wool,"},{"time":502309,"text":"alone and without much stimulation,"},{"time":503876,"text":"not only does it not thrive,"},{"time":505487,"text":"but it will often develop strange,"},{"time":507244,"text":"repetitive behaviors."},{"time":508818,"text":"This naturally sociable animal"},{"time":511437,"text":"will lose its ability to bond with other mice,"},{"time":513880,"text":"even becoming aggressive when introduced to them."},{"time":518075,"text":"However, mice reared in what we called"},{"time":520137,"text":"an enriched environment,"},{"time":521643,"text":"a large habitation with other mice"},{"time":523854,"text":"with wheels and ladders and areas to explore,"},{"time":527284,"text":"demonstrate neurogenesis,"},{"time":528869,"text":"the birth of new brain cells,"},{"time":531169,"text":"and as we showed, they also perform better"},{"time":533483,"text":"on a range of learning and memory tasks."},{"time":536200,"text":"Now, they don't develop morality to the point of"},{"time":538630,"text":"carrying the shopping bags of little old mice"},{"time":540390,"text":"across the street,"},{"time":542611,"text":"but their improved environment results in healthy,"},{"time":545354,"text":"sociable behavior."},{"time":547267,"text":"Mice reared in a standard cage, by contrast,"},{"time":550210,"text":"not dissimilar, you might say, from a prison cell,"},{"time":552675,"text":"have dramatically lower levels of new neurons"},{"time":555976,"text":"in the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557603,"text":"It is now clear that the amygdala of mammals,"},{"time":560419,"text":"including primates like us,"},{"time":561925,"text":"can show neurogenesis."},{"time":564437,"text":"In some areas of the brain,"},{"time":565723,"text":"more than 20 percent of cells are newly formed."},{"time":569418,"text":"We're just beginning to understand"},{"time":571677,"text":"what exact function these cells have,"},{"time":573771,"text":"but what it implies is that the brain is capable"},{"time":576697,"text":"of extraordinary change way into adulthood."},{"time":581890,"text":"However, our brains are also"},{"time":583624,"text":"exquisitely sensitive to stress in our environment."},{"time":587264,"text":"Stress hormones, glucocorticoids,"},{"time":589814,"text":"released by the brain,"},{"time":591364,"text":"suppress the growth of these new cells."},{"time":594925,"text":"The more stress, the less brain development,"},{"time":597473,"text":"which in turn causes less adaptability"},{"time":601941,"text":"and causes higher stress levels."},{"time":604684,"text":"This is the interplay between nature and nurture"},{"time":608469,"text":"in real time in front of our eyes."},{"time":612174,"text":"When you think about it,"},{"time":614241,"text":"it is ironic that our current solution"},{"time":616616,"text":"for people with stressed amygdalae"},{"time":618542,"text":"is to place them in an environment"},{"time":620334,"text":"that actually inhibits any chance of further growth."},{"time":624663,"text":"Of course, imprisonment is a necessary part"},{"time":627150,"text":"of the criminal justice system"},{"time":629570,"text":"and of protecting society."},{"time":631335,"text":"Our research does not suggest"},{"time":632972,"text":"that criminals should submit their MRI scans"},{"time":635189,"text":"as evidence in court"},{"time":636611,"text":"and get off the hook because\nthey've got a faulty amygdala."},{"time":640269,"text":"The evidence is actually the other way."},{"time":642342,"text":"Because our brains are capable of change,"},{"time":645193,"text":"we need to take responsibility for our actions,"},{"time":647691,"text":"and they need to take responsibility"},{"time":649543,"text":"for their rehabilitation."},{"time":652971,"text":"One way such rehabilitation might work"},{"time":654775,"text":"is through restorative justice programs."},{"time":658068,"text":"Here victims, if they choose to participate,"},{"time":660397,"text":"and perpetrators meet face to face"},{"time":662638,"text":"in safe, structured encounters,"},{"time":665338,"text":"and the perpetrator is encouraged"},{"time":667168,"text":"to take responsibility for their actions,"},{"time":669137,"text":"and the victim plays an active role in the process."},{"time":672366,"text":"In such a setting, the perpetrator can see,"},{"time":675237,"text":"perhaps for the first time,"},{"time":677572,"text":"the victim as a real person"},{"time":679976,"text":"with thoughts and feelings and a genuine"},{"time":681645,"text":"emotional response."},{"time":683483,"text":"This stimulates the amygdala"},{"time":685374,"text":"and may be a more effective rehabilitative practice"},{"time":688925,"text":"than simple incarceration."},{"time":691991,"text":"Such programs won't work for everyone,"},{"time":693576,"text":"but for many, it could be a way"},{"time":696265,"text":"to break the frozen sea within."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700626,"text":"So what can we do now?"},{"time":703385,"text":"How can we apply this knowledge?"},{"time":705897,"text":"I'd like to leave you with"},{"time":708218,"text":"three lessons that I learned."},{"time":709963,"text":"The first thing that I learned was that"},{"time":712133,"text":"we need to change our mindset."},{"time":713659,"text":"Since Wormwood Scrubs was built 130 years ago,"},{"time":716808,"text":"society has advanced in virtually every aspect,"},{"time":719923,"text":"in the way we run our schools, our hospitals."},{"time":723337,"text":"Yet the moment we speak about prisons,"},{"time":725420,"text":"it's as though we're back in Dickensian times,"},{"time":728316,"text":"if not medieval times."},{"time":730540,"text":"For too long, I believe,"},{"time":732774,"text":"we've allowed ourselves to be persuaded"},{"time":736439,"text":"of the false notion that human \nnature cannot change,"},{"time":739481,"text":"and as a society, it's costing us dearly."},{"time":743144,"text":"We know that the brain is\ncapable of extraordinary change,"},{"time":747020,"text":"and the best way to achieve that,"},{"time":750059,"text":"even in adults, is to change and modulate"},{"time":752471,"text":"our environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754266,"text":"The second thing I have learned"},{"time":757151,"text":"is that we need to create an alliance"},{"time":759777,"text":"of people who believe that science is integral"},{"time":763278,"text":"to bringing about social change."},{"time":765560,"text":"It's easy enough for a neuroscientist to place"},{"time":768533,"text":"a high-security inmate in an MRI scanner."},{"time":770712,"text":"Well actually, that turns out not to be so easy,"},{"time":773220,"text":"but ultimately what we want to show"},{"time":775879,"text":"is whether we're able to\nreduce the reoffending rates."},{"time":779647,"text":"In order to answer complex questions like that,"},{"time":782368,"text":"we need people of different backgrounds --"},{"time":785019,"text":"lab-based scientists and clinicians,"},{"time":787223,"text":"social workers and policy makers,"},{"time":789613,"text":"philanthropists and human rights activists ‚Äî"},{"time":792236,"text":"to work together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794162,"text":"Finally, I believe we need"},{"time":795849,"text":"to change our own amygdalae,"},{"time":797487,"text":"because this issue goes to the heart"},{"time":800268,"text":"not just of who Joe is,"},{"time":802039,"text":"but who we are."},{"time":803951,"text":"We need to change our view of Joe"},{"time":806931,"text":"as someone wholly irredeemable,"},{"time":810733,"text":"because if we see Joe as wholly irredeemable,"},{"time":814243,"text":"how is he going to see himself as any different?"},{"time":818523,"text":"In another decade, Joe will be released"},{"time":820394,"text":"from Wormwood Scrubs."},{"time":823063,"text":"Will he be among the 70 percent of inmates"},{"time":825980,"text":"who end up reoffending"},{"time":827474,"text":"and returning to the prison system?"},{"time":830256,"text":"Wouldn't it be better if, while serving his sentence,"},{"time":832892,"text":"Joe was able to train his amygdala,"},{"time":834818,"text":"which would stimulate the growth of new brain cells"},{"time":837172,"text":"and connections,"},{"time":838453,"text":"so that he will be able to face the world"},{"time":841049,"text":"once he gets released?"},{"time":843169,"text":"Surely, that would be in the interest of all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849549,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":852800,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}